com.locuslabs.sdk.maps.model

Class Marker.Icon

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.locuslabs.sdk.maps.model.Marker.Icon
  • Enclosing interface:
    Marker

    public static class Marker.Icon
extends java.lang.Object
    Icon Required url - the url of the icon image Optional anchor - the point on the icon image which the marker will be positioned at. default: center of bottom edge of Icon origin - the position of the image within a sprite, if a sprite is provided. default: (0, 0) scaledSize - the final size of the image after scaling. aspect ratio is not preserved. rotation - the angle by which to rotate the icon, expressed clockwise in degrees. default: 0 size - the rectangular display portion of the image or sprite. required when using sprites. default: size from the origin to the bottom right corner of the image/sprite.

      • url

        public Marker.Icon url(java.lang.String url)
        Sets the URL for the image. For example "images/map_icon_pin_grab.png" originates in the locuslabs-js-sdk as "dist/android/images/map_icon_pin_grab.png". The locuslabs-js-sdk build command ("make dist") may not be required to get the file into the proper location. The locuslabs-android-sdk build command ("./gradlew dist") copies it into several places: ./app/build/intermediates/merged_assets/staging/mergeStagingAssets/out/locuslabs/js-sdk/images/map_icon_pin_grab.png ./app/build/intermediates/merged_assets/release/mergeReleaseAssets/out/locuslabs/js-sdk/images/map_icon_pin_grab.png ./app/build/intermediates/merged_assets/debug/mergeDebugAssets/out/locuslabs/js-sdk/images/map_icon_pin_grab.png ./sdk/build/intermediates/library_assets/staging/packageStagingAssets/out/locuslabs/js-sdk/images/map_icon_pin_grab.png ./sdk/build/intermediates/library_assets/release/packageReleaseAssets/out/locuslabs/js-sdk/images/map_icon_pin_grab.png ./sdk/build/intermediates/library_assets/debug/packageDebugAssets/out/locuslabs/js-sdk/images/map_icon_pin_grab.png
        Parameters:
        url - the new URL for the Marker
        Returns:
        the Icon itself
